The paper discusses a ranked retrieval model for search query processing in web databases, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research. The paper also presents a third-party service that enables the on-the-fly processing of queries with any user-specified ranking functions, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
